## Mandatory Card Lifecycle Workflow

Every execution card MUST pass through ALL workflow lanes in order. No lane may
be skipped.

## Lane Semantics

| Lane | Movement semantic |
|------|-------------------|
| `Info → Backlog` | Card is scoped and ready for implementation. |
| `Backlog → In Progress` | Manager assigns work to a worker. |
| `In Progress → Review` | Manager MUST run `codex_wp review` before the move. |
| `Review → Simplification` | Manager MUST run `$code-simplification` or record a truthful no-change verdict. |
| `Simplification → Auto-commit` | Manager MUST run `$auto-commit` and capture commit evidence. |
| `Auto-commit → Done` | Manager performs final verification and sends `$notify-me`. |
| `Review → Blocked` | Use when 3 review cycles still return P0/P1 issues or a real blocker prevents progress. |
| `Blocked → Backlog` | Use only after operator or manager resolves the blocker and the card is ready for another real attempt. |

### Lane-by-lane transition protocol

Each transition is atomic: Trello move + Trello comment happen in the same
action chain.

#### Transition 1: Backlog -> In Progress

| Step | Who | Action | Tool |
|------|-----|--------|------|
| 1a | Manager | Check Trello board state for card location and dependencies | `trello card-info` |
| 1b | Manager | Build task prompt from card description + technical details | text assembly |
| 1c | Manager | Dispatch task to worker pane | `p2p --pane-id WORKER --submit "<prompt>"` |
| 1d | Manager | Move card to In Progress | `trello move-card` |
| 1e | Manager | Add Trello comment with dispatch evidence | `trello add-comment` |

#### Transition 2: In Progress -> Review

**Trigger:** worker sends `TAHIR_DONE_<task-id>` via p2p.

| Step | Who | Action | Tool |
|------|-----|--------|------|
| 2a | Manager | Receive completion signal | p2p inbox |
| 2b | Manager | Verify implementation files exist | `git status` |
| 2c | Manager | Run code review | `codex_wp review <files>` or `kimi` review |
| 2d | Manager | If P0/P1 issues found -> send fixes to worker | `p2p --pane-id WORKER` |
| 2e | Manager | When review passes, move card to Review | `trello move-card` |
| 2f | Manager | Save review report to file | write tool |
| 2g | Manager | Add Trello comment with review verdict | `trello add-comment` |

#### Review Back-and-Forth Escape Hatch

- keep a per-card review cycle count
- after 3 review cycles still producing P0/P1 issues, stop the loop
- move the card to `Blocked` when that list exists
- add a simplified Russian blocker comment
- if `Blocked` does not exist, keep the card in `Review` with the truthful blocker comment
- resume only through `Blocked → Backlog` after the blocker is actually resolved

#### Transition 3: Review -> Simplification

| Step | Who | Action | Tool |
|------|-----|--------|------|
| 3a | Manager | Run simplification pass | `$code-simplification` skill |
| 3b | Manager | If simplification found -> apply changes | edit/write |
| 3c | Manager | Move card to Simplification | `trello move-card` |
| 3d | Manager | Add Trello comment with simplification result | `trello add-comment` |

#### Transition 4: Simplification -> Auto-commit

| Step | Who | Action | Tool |
|------|-----|--------|------|
| 4a | Manager | Stage all changed/new files | `git add <files>` |
| 4b | Manager | Create commit with descriptive message | `git commit` |
| 4c | Manager | Record commit hash | `git log --oneline -1` |
| 4d | Manager | Move card to Auto-commit | `trello move-card` |
| 4e | Manager | Add Trello comment with commit hash + subject | `trello add-comment` |

#### Transition 5: Auto-commit -> Done

| Step | Who | Action | Tool |
|------|-----|--------|------|
| 5a | Manager | Verify card passed all previous lanes | check comments |
| 5b | Manager | Move card to Done | `trello move-card` |
| 5c | Manager | Add final Trello comment | `trello add-comment` |
| 5d | Manager | Send Mattermost notification | `$notify-me` skill |
| 5e | Manager | Advance to next task | re-enter at Transition 1 |

## Trello Comment Style

- Use simplified Russian only
- Use bullet points only
- Keep each bullet to 3-5 words when practical
- Keep comments human-facing and easy to scan

## Info Column Structure

- `Info` is an archive and reference list, not a workflow lane
- Keep one aggregate mockups card such as `<emoji> Mockups Gallery`
- Keep one aggregate audio card such as `<emoji> Voice Summaries Archive`
- These cards mirror links from per-epic info cards and never carry epic labels
- These cards never move through workflow lanes

## Epic Runner Cards

- Live in `Epics Runners` only
- Never carry epic labels
- Never move through workflow lanes
- Never become actionable task cards
- Runner script is the mandatory epic execution path
- Launcher header should reference project-root `TRELLO.md`
